Classical swine fever, Colombia
----------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 13 Jun 2014 from Dr Luis Humberto Martinez Lacouture, Gerente General, Instituto Colombiano Agropecuario (ICA), Ministerio de Agricultura y Desarrollo Rural, Bogota , Colombia

Summary
Report type: follow-up No. 8
Date of start of the event: 1 Jun 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 8 Jun 2013
Report date: 13 Jun 2014
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 26 Jun 2007
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Classical swine fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (basic), Laboratory (advanced), Necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (3)
Outbreak 1: Carrizal, Los Martinez, Chiriguana, Cesar
Date of start of the outbreak: 11 Apr 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 19 / 8 / 5 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Swine backyard holdings in grazing management. Young animals not vaccinated. Direct contact with other animal populations in the neighbouring farms. Animals fed with oil palm culture surpluses.

Outbreak 2: Centre of Santa Ana, Casco urbano, Santa Ana, Magdalena
Date of start of the outbreak: 13 Apr 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 18 / 8 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Backyard holdings in the centre of the municipality. Animals fed with swill feed. Vaccination had been suspended on 1 Jun 2013. Direct contact with other animals.

Outbreak 3: Centre of Cano Hondo, Casco urbano, Talaigua Nuevo, Bolivar
Date of start of the outbreak: 27 Apr 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 23 / 9 / 6 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Two outbreaks in the centre of the hamlet Cano Hondo within the municipality of Talaigua Nueva. Backyard holdings in grazing management where swine are fed with swill feed, direct contact with other animals. Area where vaccination had been suspended.

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 3
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 60 / 25 / 12 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Swine / 41.67 percent / 20 percent / 48 percent / 20 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter.

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: introduction of new live animals; illegal movement of animals; contact with infected animal(s) at grazing/watering; swill feeding; fomites (humans, vehicles, feed, etc.)

Epidemiological comments: The outbreak was reported by the owner. It is limited to this farm. No other cases. Active epidemiological surveillance is carried out exhaustively in a 5-km radius zone around the outbreak and in a 5-km surveillance zone; daily follow-up inspections are done, and no other sick animals have been found in the monitored areas. Vaccination is forbidden in this zone since 31 May 2013.

Control measures:
Measures applied: quarantine; movement control inside the country; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); no treatment of affected animals; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)
Administrative division / Species / Total vaccinated / Details
Magdalena / swine / 9654 / up to 11 Jun 2014
Cesar / swine / 20 848 / -
Bolivar / swine / 3987 / up to 11 Jun 2014

Measures to be applied: no other measures
Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Veterinary Diagnosis Laboratory (National laboratory) / Swine / real-time reverse transcriptase/polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 11 Apr 2014 / Positive
National Veterinary Diagnosis Laboratory (National laboratory) / Swine / real-time reverse transcriptase/polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 5 May 2014 / Positive
National Veterinary Diagnosis Laboratory (National laboratory) / Swine / real-time reverse transcriptase/polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 8 May 2014 / Positive
National Veterinary Diagnosis Laboratory (National laboratory) / Swine / virus isolation / 6 Mar 2014 / Positive

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

